labor_categories.labor_category: Face to Face Interpretation-Consecutive

raw_data.title: Face to Face Interpretation-Consecutive
raw_data.description: Provide a person to perform interpreting face to face to a physical location as specified by the client.  The person will be chosen from a large pool of interpreters that together speak over 200 languages as well as Sign Languages, and who specialize in a variety of subject matters; this includes medical and federally certified linguists for a variety of settings.  Interpreters are quality tested to be professional and fit in to the environment rather than stick out.  Choice will be based on a variety of factors languages, specialties, and proximity to the location.  This person will fluently interpret the languages necessary so as to enable the parties to communicate optimally and achieve all other performance goals.  This service is face to face and only interpreters tested who prove to have the mental dexterity necessary to perform consecutive interpretation will be chosen. Consecutive interpreting within the continental U.S. for common languages. All interpretation requests are subject to a minimum commitment of 2 hours.

labor_categories.labor_category: Sign Language Interpretation

raw_data.title: Sign Language Interpretation
raw_data.description: We are able to provide all services under this SIN, as outlined by GSA: ASL/English, Manually Coded English, Pigeon Signed English (PSE), Contact Sign, International Sign Other services include Closed Captioning, Voice-Overs, Textbook or Audio Script Translation, Website (HTML) and Online Document Translation with typesetting services, Telephone Services (TDD and TTY), Close-Captioning, Deaf Interpreting, Tactile, and Cued English Transliteration. Braille, Text Adaptation, and Section 508 Compliant Language Services. These services may take place at a physical location as specified by the client, or through various platforms including VTEL, Videophone and more. The interpreter(s) will be chosen from a large pool based on a variety of factors as specified by the client – including type of service, subject matter, and proximity- in order to achieve all of the client performance goals. All interpretation requests are subject to a minimum commitment of 2 hours.

labor_categories.labor_category: VRI - First 15 Minutes

raw_data.title: VRI - First 15 Minutes
raw_data.description: VRI is a sign language interpreting service, provided over the internet via video. Providers have extensive experience and hold the necessary certifications with the NCRA. They possess the experience and knowledge to provide high quality and accurate services to include all the spoken words and environmental sounds empowering the consumer to decide what is important to them. We perform a rigorous screening to ensure that our reporters provide our clients with professional, detailed and dependable service. Trusted Translations can provide services with both standard and short notice requests.  See contract for minimum hourly requirements, and required notice.
